						<div class="postbody">I briefly skimmed (did not really look at in depth) the code yesterday while I wasn't feeling very well, and I saw some spots where it looks like you're re-setting PPUScroll/$2005 to some value like $FF.  Possibly this needs to be adjusted as to not include the area of the screen where the status bar is?  Just a thought.<br /><br />Code in question is part of the IRQ/BRK handler:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;LDA #$FF<br />&nbsp;STA IRQDisable<br />&nbsp;STA scrollX<br />&nbsp;STA PPUScroll<br />&nbsp;LDA #$00<br />&nbsp;STA PPUScroll<br /></div></div>

